FHS students. Remember to not come to school if you have the following symptoms.

5. Sore throat

Stay safe and healthy!

Friona High School Band
July 21 at 4:14 PM ¬∑

Dear Chieftain Band Member,

We have new information from UIL that has sent me back to the drawing board with summer band. I have shortened the amount of practices due to the amount of things we can do and to keep us from being outside during the extreme heat of the afternoon. This makes each practice even more important.

Remember to bring

A FACE MASK
A WATER BOTTLE
YOUR MEDICAL HISTORY FORM
TENNIS SHOES

If you have any questions or conflicts TALK TO ME. Communication key! crackley@frionaisd.com
Please watch our facebook page for any future adjustments.

post_text:
Friona ISD and Community:
Thank You for your patience as we try to navigate through all of the unknowns for the upcoming school year. The information we receive from the Governor, TEA, UIL, cDC and others changes almost daily. We are keeping the safety of our students,staff and our community our top priority.
We will be sending out information about registration, protocols, and the upcoming school year within the next week.

Jimmy Burns
Friona ISD Superintendent

Senior Spotlight
Drew,
Watching you grow has been our greatest pleasure. We know that you are ready to make your mark on the world. Seeing you mature, watching you accomplish your goals and witnessing you stand up when life has knocked you down, have been some of the proudest moments of our lives. Continue to walk with God and follow your dreams. We are proud of the young man you have become. We will always be your home!
Love,
Mom and Dad

Senior Spotlight

Carly... you have the world beneath your feet. You are a joy to watch as you set your mind on a goal ahead and go conquer it. Nothing is out of reach when you keep the correct focus. Remember... ‚ÄúIn all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will continue to direct your path.‚Äù Prov 3:6. The world cannot stop you and has no hold on you. So as your high school days end and your next phase begins... remember WHO you are as you find your way. You are an unbelievably special young lady and everywhere you go you leave your mark. Your heart is pure and kind and you are so full of Joy. Continue to walk your walk and show the world who you are!! We are so proud of you and look forward to watching you excel in this next stage of life!! We love you more!!!

Love Mom and Dad

Senior Spotlight

Nathan has been an active member of band and powerlifting all 4 years of high school. He has also participated in track, choir, and tennis. He is an outstanding trumpet player. He has made an All Region band all 4 years of high school, as well as made state solo and ensemble all 4 years. He is a 2 time TMEA Texas Music Scholar. He also is a 4 year regional powerlifting qualifier.

Nathan will be attending West Texas A&M University this fall. He will be majoring in Music Education.

We cannot begin to express how proud we are of our senior, as well as all the other 2020 Seniors ‚ô•Ô∏è

#2020seniors #2020strong

post_text:
Senior Spotlight

Adaline Ruth White has attended Friona schools for 13 years. Her favorite activities included band, the musical, One Act Play, floriculture in FFA, and 4-H. She also volunteered with Parmer Paws, sweat suits for seniors, and SnackPac4Kids. Her hobbies are listening to music and playing her guitar. Adaline loves animals, especially cats. She has been called on many occasions to rescue a lost or abandoned kitten. Her dad and I are very proud of all her accomplishments and the amazing young woman she has become. We are excited for the next chapter in her life beginning at the University of North Texas in the fall.

FISD and Aramark will now be offering breakfast and lunch for any student 18 years and younger seven days a week. In the interest of public health, the City of Houston and the Houston Health Department have ordered the Houston Livestock Show and Rodeo‚Ñ¢ to close. The grounds will close at 4 p.m. The Rodeo will respectfully and dutifully comply with the City‚Äôs order.

The Rodeo is deeply saddened; however, the safety and well-being of our guests and our community is our top priority. Out of precaution, the City has decided that this is the best course of action for our community.

For more information regarding this announcement, visit rodeohouston.com/2020

From FISD Administration

Get a head start and skip the crowd at registration next week!

Online Registration has been opened in Parent Portal. You may go in and register your returning children. If you go online and register them you will NOT have to come to the registration at the junior high next Monday or Tuesday. You will not need to print out any documents or a confirmation to turn in. When you log in to parent portal close the box that pops up to say registration is open and click on the 2019-2020 registration button under each child's name to complete and update your child's registration.

Here is the link to Parent Portal

https://txsuite01.region16.net/tc185903/Login.aspx
